Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. 9:51 AM Prosecuting attorney Brian H. Wright Aty appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Robert G Clark appeared in court, in custody, Attorney Dustin Matthew Rockow appeared in court for Robert G Clark. 
9:52 Jurors seated. Court reads jury instructions. 9:57 Opening statement by State. 10:04 Opening Statement by Defense. 10:06 Sidebar; jurors excused; court resumes outside the presence of the jury. Attorney Rockow relates of phone call appearance by the Defendant. State relates. Argument by parties. Court relates. Defense relates on motion in limine and requests the court not grant any evidence from the PA case, only the PJ case, as that was the case disclosed. State relates and request the court allow the evidence. Court finds the evidence relevant but relates of evidence being disclosed. Defense relates regarding request for electronic access to PA file, PJ case file was given. Court relates of difference of PA/PJ case file and the difference in documents. Court finds that the State was to provide any documents or evidence to Defense. 10:33 Court in recess to review supreme court case. 10:52 Court resumes outside the presence of the jury. Court references Wisconsin Supreme Court Case 19WI11. Court finds any evidence that state intended to be introduced was to be turned over to Defense. Court finds there is a discovery violation. Court grants the motion to prohibit the introduction of the statements or initial proceedings prior to the findings of facts conclusions of law and judgment within the PJ case. 10:57 Court in recess. 11:28 Case resumes outside the presence of the jury.  State relates this case will be a deferred agreement. State requests the jury be released, case would remain open and a DPA would be filed for a period of 12 months from today. State will draft the DPA  for courts approval and case will be recalled today to enter that agreement. State indicates count 2 will be dismissed.  State would move to release on own recognizance dismissing the cash bond previously ordered. 

Review hearing set to see status of DPA. Court relates Defendant would need to still provide the court with his current address. Court orders that the defendant  must notify of any change of address or phone number, along with any change of employer, if unemployed must seek work (5 job applications per week with a monthly job log to the CSA (20 job applications per month) job search efforts to be provided to CSA, must register with local job agency. Defendant may appear by zoom video if in compliance. If defendant is not in compliance must appear in person for 1/23/23 court hearing. 

11:46 Jurors seated; court resumes; 11:47 jurors excused. 11:48 Court resumes outside the presence of the jury. Court relates of bond. Attorney Rockow relates. State relates. Court relates and grants the request and releases the defendant on his own recognizance upon acceptance of DPA. Court orders the parties to submit the DPA. Court dismisses the bond. State moves to dismiss count 2. Court grants dismissal of count 2. State will file the DPA on count 1.
